IDEAS FOR PLATFORMER LEVELS
============================
Game Context: Floating city held aloft by the Heart Crystal. The crystal cracked
~100 years ago. Chunks of the city keep breaking off and falling into the Void.
Player character can hear crystals sing. Goal: collect crystal pieces calling to you.

Reference tileset: grass/dirt platformer tileset with green grass surface,
brown-maroon dirt body (wavy zigzag texture), decorative grass blades, hanging
vines, corner/edge/platform pieces, and small gem collectibles.

All prompts below are written for AI tileset restyling tools. Each prompt
describes how to remap every visual element of the reference tileset onto a
new level theme.

================================================================================
LEVEL 1 — THE VERDANT REMNANTS (Starting Area / Tutorial Zone)
================================================================================
Theme: The last healthy gardens on the floating city. Lush and alive, but subtle
signs of decay hint that something is wrong. Tiny crystal veins peek through the
soil. This is "home" — warm and inviting but bittersweet.

PROMPT:
Tileset restyle edit, the green grass area should be kept as vibrant green grass
but with slightly overgrown, wild look — longer individual blades with a few
tiny pale-blue crystal shards poking up through the grass like small flowers.
The grass edge should have a soft, rounded organic feel, not perfectly straight.
Add a very subtle golden-hour warm tint to the green.

The brown dirt area should be changed to a rich, warm earth tone — think dark
umber with a slight reddish warmth. Replace the wavy zigzag texture with a
layered sediment look: horizontal bands of slightly different earth tones with
occasional tiny pale-blue crystal veins running through like thin roots. The
veins should be subtle, not overpowering — just a hint that crystals run
through everything here.

The decorative grass blades should be restyled as wild meadow grass — varied
heights, some with tiny seed heads, a couple with small blue crystal buds
mixed in. Keep them green but slightly more varied in shade than the platform
grass (some yellow-green, some deep green).

The hanging vines should be restyled as trailing ivy with small rounded leaves.
A few leaves near the tips should have a faint blue-white glow, as if the
crystal energy seeps into the plants. The vines should look healthy and full.

The gem collectibles should be restyled as small crystal shards in different
colors — pale blue (common), soft violet (uncommon), warm amber (rare), and
one deep rose-pink (the Heart Crystal fragment color). They should have a
subtle inner glow and a tiny sparkle highlight.

Overall it should have a retro handheld gaming style with a warm, inviting
Studio Ghibli-meets-GBA vibe. Think the opening village in a classic RPG —
peaceful but with an underlying melancholy. 16-bit pixel art, soft but
saturated palette.


================================================================================
LEVEL 2 — THE CRUMBLING EDGE (Early-Game Challenge Zone)
================================================================================
Theme: The outer rim of the floating city where chunks are actively breaking
away. The ground is cracked and unstable. Grass is patchy and struggling. You
can see sky through fissures in the earth. This is where players first feel
the danger of the world falling apart.

PROMPT:
Tileset restyle edit, the green grass area should be changed to sparse, patchy
dry grass — pale green and straw-yellow mixed together, with visible cracks in
the ground showing through between clumps. The grass edge should look jagged
and broken, like the earth has been fractured. Some sections should have no
grass at all, just bare cracked stone showing through.

The brown dirt area should be changed to cracked grey-brown stone with visible
fracture lines running through it. Replace the wavy zigzag texture with a
cracked earth pattern — irregular fracture lines with faint blue-white crystal
light glowing from deep within the cracks. The edges of broken pieces should
show exposed layers of compressed earth and stone. Some areas should look like
they could break away at any moment.

The decorative grass blades should be restyled as dried, bent grass tufts and
small bits of rubble. A few should be tiny chunks of floating debris hovering
just above the ground (held up by residual crystal energy). Mix in a couple of
small warning-sign posts or broken fence fragments to sell the "danger zone"
feeling.

The hanging vines should be restyled as crumbling earth and dangling roots
exposed by the breaking ground. Some roots should have crystal veins wrapped
around them, glowing faintly. A couple should be dripping small particles
downward, implying the ground is actively shedding material into the void.

The gem collectibles should keep the same crystal shard style from Level 1 but
with slightly more intense glow — the crystals are more exposed and active here
near the edge where the land is fracturing.

Overall it should have a retro handheld gaming style with a tense, precarious
cliff-edge vibe. Think the crumbling platforms in Castlevania or the unstable
ground in Celeste. Desaturated compared to Level 1 — muted greens, dusty
browns, cold greys, with the crystal glow providing the only vibrant color.


================================================================================
LEVEL 3 — THE VOID DESCENT (Mid-Game Vertical Level)
================================================================================
Theme: The player descends through open sky and floating debris below the city.
Platforms are chunks of fallen earth suspended in mid-air by residual crystal
energy. The "sky" is a deep gradient from pale blue above to dark indigo-black
below — the Void. Everything feels weightless and lonely.

PROMPT:
Tileset restyle edit, the green grass area should be changed to dead, grey-brown
dried moss clinging to the tops of floating rock chunks. It should look like it
was once living grass that died when this piece broke away from the city. Some
patches should be completely bare, with just bare stone showing. The edge should
be rough and irregular — these are torn-off chunks, not natural ground.

The brown dirt area should be changed to dark grey-blue stone — the raw
underside of the floating city's foundation. Replace the wavy zigzag texture
with a rough, fractured rock texture showing exposed crystal veins that glow
with a cold blue-white light. The crystals are what keep these chunks floating.
The overall tone should be dark and cold, with the crystal glow providing eerie
illumination from within.

The decorative grass blades should be restyled as small floating debris
particles — tiny rocks, dust motes, and crystal fragments hovering around the
platforms. Some should have faint glow trails suggesting slow movement. A couple
should be small dead plant remnants (dried stems, curled leaves) frozen in
mid-float.

The hanging vines should be restyled as crystalline formations growing downward
from the rock — stalactite-like crystal growths with a cold blue-purple glow.
They should look sharp and geometric, in contrast to the organic vines in
Level 1. Some should have small particles drifting off their tips, dissolving
into the void below.

The gem collectibles should have a stronger, more desperate glow here — the
crystal shards are calling louder to the player. Add a visible aura or pulse
effect around each one. The Heart Crystal fragment (rose-pink) should have
small orbiting particles around it.

Overall it should have a retro handheld gaming style with a lonely, haunting
atmosphere like the sky levels in Shovel Knight or the outer-space segments in
Cave Story. Deep blue-indigo-black color palette with cold crystal glows as
accent. Feeling of vast empty space and quiet danger.


