LEVEL 6 — THE CLOUD CANOPY (Traversal / Breather Level)
================================================================================
Theme: The cloud layer that surrounds the floating city. Soft, ethereal
platforms made of condensed cloud-stuff held together by crystal energy.
A calm, dreamlike level between intense ones. The player is literally
walking on clouds and light.

PROMPT:
Tileset restyle edit, the green grass area should be replaced with a soft,
fluffy cloud-top surface — pure white and pale lavender with subtle cotton-like
texture. The edge should be rounded, billowy, and soft — no hard lines at all.
Small wisps of cloud should curl up from the surface like steam. Add very faint
rainbow-prismatic highlights where crystal energy holds the cloud together.

The brown dirt area should be changed to the interior of dense cloud — slightly
darker than the surface, in pale grey-lavender and soft blue tones. Replace the
wavy zigzag texture with a soft, swirling mist texture — gentle curves and
wisps suggesting dense vapor. Embed faint golden-white crystal lattice lines
running through the cloud body, implying that crystal energy is what gives
these clouds enough substance to stand on.

The decorative grass blades should be restyled as small cloud wisps and tiny
floating ice crystals — delicate, barely-there details that catch the light.
A few should be small prismatic sparkles (like sun hitting ice). Keep them
very light and airy — minimal visual weight.

The hanging vines should be restyled as trailing cloud wisps and gentle
waterfalls of mist pouring off the cloud platforms. They should be wispy,
translucent, and soft. A couple should have embedded crystal sparkles drifting
downward through the mist like glitter in slow motion.

The gem collectibles should have a warm, golden glow here — standing out
against the cool whites and lavenders. They should look like captured sunlight
embedded in crystal. The contrast of warm crystal against cool cloud makes them
immediately visible and inviting.

Overall it should have a retro handheld gaming style with a dreamy, peaceful
Sky Sanctuary Zone vibe (Sonic) crossed with the cloud levels in Kid Icarus.
Soft pastel palette — whites, lavenders, pale blues, with warm golden crystal
accents. The feeling is serene, weightless, and magical.


