LEVEL 7 — THE HEART CHAMBER (Final Area / Endgame)
================================================================================
Theme: The innermost chamber of the floating city where the cracked Heart
Crystal resides. Reality itself is unstable here. The environment shifts between
beautiful and corrupted. Crystal energy saturates everything — the ground
pulses, the air shimmers, geometry warps subtly. This is the climax.

PROMPT:
Tileset restyle edit, the green grass area should be replaced with a living
crystal surface — smooth, faceted, rose-pink and deep magenta crystal that
pulses with a visible heartbeat-like glow. The edge should be sharp and
geometric, with fractured facets catching light at different angles. Thin veins
of bright white energy should run along the surface like a circulatory system.
In some tiles, the surface should show cracks with intense white-pink light
bleeding through — the Heart Crystal's damage is everywhere.

The brown dirt area should be changed to deep, dark crystal matrix — nearly
black with dense networks of glowing rose-pink and hot-white crystal veins
running through it. Replace the wavy zigzag texture with an angular, fractured
crystalline structure — geometric planes and sharp angles, like the inside of
a shattered gemstone. The glow should pulse subtly, like a heartbeat. Some
sections should show corruption — areas where the crystal has gone dark or
where cracks emit unstable flickering light.

The decorative grass blades should be restyled as crystal spires and energy
arcs — tall, sharp crystal formations that crackle with energy at their tips.
Some should be intact and beautiful (symmetrical, glowing steadily). Others
should be cracked and unstable (asymmetrical, flickering, with fragments
floating off them). This contrast tells the story of the Heart Crystal's
state — once magnificent, now breaking.

The hanging vines should be restyled as streams of pure crystal energy flowing
downward — like liquid light pouring off the platforms. They should be bright
rose-pink and white, almost too bright to look at. Some streams should be
stuttering and flickering, breaking into droplets, showing the instability.
Others should flow smooth and steady where the Heart Crystal's power still
holds.

The gem collectibles here should be Heart Crystal fragments specifically —
all rose-pink with intense internal glow and visible energy radiating outward
in concentric pulse rings. They should be the most visually dramatic
collectibles in the game. These are the pieces the player has been working
toward the entire time.

Overall it should have a retro handheld gaming style with an intense, climactic
final-dungeon energy — think the final areas of Hyper Light Drifter or the
Heart of the Hollow Knight. Deep blacks and dark magentas with searing rose-pink
and white crystal energy. The vibe is beautiful but unstable, powerful but
breaking. Everything about this tileset should say "the heart of something
magnificent is dying, and you might be able to save it."


